45 Internal Revenue Code, that delivers electricity for no exchange of consideration or
46 payment, and that is located upon federal interstate right of way, or (3) an
47 exemption certificate has been obtained on forms furnished by the Department of
48 Revenue showing that there is no highway use of such fuels and the person
49 obtaining such fuel is not a reseller of such fuels. Each exemption certificate shall
50 be valid for a period of not more than three years and shall be kept by the distributor
51 as one of the records specified in Code Section 48-9-8. It shall be the responsibility
52 of the purchaser to notify the distributor when the purchaser is no longer qualified
53 for the nonhighway exemption. All applicable taxes must shall be charged the
54 purchaser until the purchaser is granted a valid distributor's license for that type of
55 motor fuel."
56 SECTION 3.
57 This Act shall become effective on January 1, 2026.
58 SECTION 4.
59 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
